{{if data.window_mode == "main"}}
<div class="item">
    <div class="itemLabel">Mode:</div>
        <div class="itemContent">
            {{:helper.link("Toggle mode", "gear", {"ui_key": "state_laws", "toggle_mode": 1}, null, 'floatRight')}}
            {{if data.freeform}}
                Freeform
            {{else}}
                Standard
            {{/if}}
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
{{if data.freeform}}
<div class="item">
    <div class="statusDisplay">
        <p><font color="red"><b>LYING ABOUT YOUR LAWSET IS AGAINST YOUR LAWS UNLESS A LAW PERMITS OR OBLIGATES YOU TO LIE</b></font></p>
        <p>
            Examples of this are Syndicate subversion (emag) and lawsets that do not force you to serve carbons,
            such as Corporate (but you'd better have a good reason.)
            <b>Asimov silicons usually can not lie about their laws.</b>
        </p>
        <p>Breaking this rule will get you bwoinked, jobbanned or worse. If you don't need to lie, use the regular State Laws functionality.</p>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="item">
    <div class="line">
        {{:helper.link("Edit", "gear", {"ui_key": "state_laws", "window_mode": "freeform_edit"}, null, 'floatRight')}}
        <h3 style="clear:left;display:inline">Currently selected laws</h3>
    </div>
    <div class="statusDisplay">
        {{for data.freeform_laws}}
            <div class="line">
                <div class="statusValue">
                    {{:value.text}}
                </div>
            </div>
        {{empty}}
            <div class="line">
                <div class="statusValue dark">(no laws selected)</div>
            </div>
        {{/for}}
    </div>
</div>
{{/if}}

{{else data.window_mode == "freeform_edit"}}
<div class="item">
    <h3>Edit laws</h3>
    <div class="statusDisplay">
        <form name="lawedit" action="?src={{:data.src}}" method="get">
            <input type="hidden" name="ui_key" value="state_laws">
            <textarea name="edited_laws" id="edited_laws" rows="10" cols="50">
                Lorem ipsum etc.
            </textarea>
            <input type="submit" value="Submit">
        </form>
    </div>
    {{:helper.link("Edit", "gear", {"ui_key": "state_laws", "window_mode": "main"})}}
</div>

{{/if}}